The paper deals with algorithms for solving parity games, which are a type of two-player game played on a directed graph. The paper uses concepts from automata theory and graph theory to analyze and improve upon existing algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also involves concepts from data structures (cs.DS), logic (cs.LO), programming languages (cs.PL), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), as it deals with algorithmic techniques for solving complex problems.
